    {
      "note_no": "17",
      "note": "Inasmuch as this is evidently an allusion to the intense tribalism of the bedouin and their \"pride of descent\" (Razi), the above verse connects with the preceding condemnation of all tribal preferences and prejudices, and with the call for their abandonment as a prerequisite of true faith. Primarily, this relates to the bedouin contemporaries of the Prophet, but its import is general and timeless."
